            "===== SAMPLE 2 =====\n",
            "\n",
            "REFERENCE:\n",
            " spinal epidural lipomatosis ( sel ) is an abnormal localized accumulation of fat tissues in the epidural space. it is strongly related with steroid administration. the symptoms of sel are various and range from back pain to paraplegia. in severe cases, decompressive laminectomy is the choice of treatment. a 32-year - old woman who had been under long - term steroid administration after suprasellar tumor resection was admitted for both leg radiating pain and weakness. she was diagnosed with sel and had a decompressive laminectomy. during the operation, we found the nerve roots were compressed by epidural fat tissues and engorged vessels. after the operation, her radiating pain was relieved and motor weakness was improved.\n",
            "\n",
            "--- BioBART ---\n",
            " spinal epidural lipomatosis ( sel ) is a rare disease that is characterized by pathologic overgrowth of lumbar or thoracic epidural fat tissue. although the etiology of sel is not known, sel has been frequently diagnosed in obese patient groups and exogenous steroid administration groups, so steroid metabolism is presumed to be related with sel.1, excessive adipural fat deposition in the spinal canal can contribute to various neurologic symptoms, such as back pain, radiculopathy, myelopathy, claudication and even cauda equina syndrome.In this case, we present a sel patient who had taken steroid hormone medicine for 20 years, after a suprasellar tumor resection. she presented with leg weakness and radiating pain on both buttock, posterior thigh & calf for 1 year. because pain and weakness in both legs was gradually aggravated during 4 months, she could not walk or stand when she was admitted. carbohydcause spinal compression and present with similar symptoms17 ). conservative managements such as exogenous dexamethasone tapering and weight loss are recommended in early sel patients while patients with severe symptoms or progressive neurologic deficits are indicated for operation1,7,9,13 ). in a study by fogel et al.7 ), seventy - seven percent of patients of the steroid group who underwent on decompressive laminectomy had symptom improvements. but in astudy by fassett et al.,6 ), the mortality rate in these patients within 1 year after surgical decompression was 22%, because of concomitant medical problems and comorbidities. consequentially, we must make a treatment plan that considers various factors,such as neurologic severity, general health, steroid therapy and lifestyle. in patients who underwent an operation for suprayllar lesions such as pituitary adenoma, supracellar meningioma, craniopharyngi\n",
            "\n",
            "--- BART ---\n",
            " spinal epidural lipomatosis ( sel ) is a rare disease that is characterized by pathologic overgrowth of lumbar or thoracic epidural fat tissue. although the etiology of sel is not known, sel has been frequently diagnosed in obese patient groups and exogenous steroid administration groups, so steroid metabolism is presumed to be related with sel. excessive epidural Fat deposition in the spinal canal can contribute to various neurologic symptoms, such as back pain, radiculopathy, myelopathy, claudication and even cauda equina syndrome. in this case, we present a sel patient who had taken steroid hormone medicine for 20 years, after a suprasellar tumor resection. she presented with leg weakness and radiating pain on both buttock, posterior thigh & calf for 1 year. because pain and weakness in both legs was gradually aggravated during 4 months, she could not walk or stand when she was admitted. prior to surgical decompression, she had been suffering from severe back pain and progressive neurologic deficits. she was also suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), which is caused by the presence of a large amount of fluid in her spinal canal. these patients are often referred to the hospital for further treatment. they all suffer from all-cause spinal compression and present with similar symptoms17 ). conservative managements such as exogenous steroids tapering and weight loss are recommended in early sel patients while patients with severe symptoms or progressive Neurologic deficits are indicated for operation1,7,9,13 ). in a study by fogel et al.7 ), seventy - seven percent of patients of the steroid group who underwent on decompressive laminectomy had symptom improvements. but in a recent study by fassett et al (6 ), the mortality rate in these patients within 1 year after surgical decompress was 22%, because of concomitant medical problems and comorbidities. consequentially,\n",
            "\n",
            "--- Falconsai ---\n",
            " spinal epidural lipomatosis ( sel ) is a rare disease that is characterized by pathologic overgrowth of lumbar or thoracic epidal fat tissue. in this review, we present a sel patient who had taken steroid hormone medicine for 20 years after a suprasellar tumor resection. she presented with leg weakness and radiating pain on both buttock, posterior thigh & calf for 1 year. because pain and weakness in both legs was gradually aggravated during 4 months, she had an operation to decompress the l5 and s1 dermatomes.resultsthe median length from the dorsum of the spinal cord to the ligamentum flavum was 11.4 mm and the median length was 9.\n",
